overview: The user initiated a task to enhance a sleep questionnaire application
  by integrating a database for storing responses, developing an admin dashboard
  for client access, and implementing an authentication mechanism. The project
  was guided by a Statement of Work. The approach involved a comprehensive
  evaluation of the existing codebase to identify missing components. Key
  decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for database
  management, updating the demographic data structure to align with SOW
  requirements while retaining existing fields, and opting for a straightforward
  password-based authentication system for the admin dashboard. The
  implementation plan detailed creating a new Prisma model for questionnaire
  responses, developing API endpoints for data submission and secure retrieval
  (including CSV export), and building the admin login page. The next steps will
  involve completing the admin dashboard and integrating the database submission
  into the main questionnaire form.
